data.enText: rate of movement/action
the rate at which sb/sth moves or travels
He reduced speed and turned sharp left.
The train began to pick up speed (= go faster) .
The car was gathering speed .

data.enText: a speed of 50 mph/80 kph

data.enText: at high/low/full/top speed
at breakneck speed (= fast in a way that is dangerous)
travelling at the speed of light/sound
the rate at which sth happens or is done
the processing speed of the computer

data.chText: 这门课的设计思路是让学生自己掌握进度。
data.enText: This course is designed so that students can progress at their own speed.

data.chText: 我们力争提高送货速度。
data.enText: We aim to increase the speed of delivery (= how quickly goods are sent) .
the quality of being quick or rapid

data.chText: 事故的原因在于速度过快。
data.enText: The accident was due to excessive speed.

data.chText: 事态发展迅速为她始料所不及。
data.enText: She was overtaken by the speed of events (= things happened more quickly than she expected) .

data.chText: 一辆汽车从他们身边疾驰而过。
data.enText: A car flashed past them at speed (= fast) .

a measurement of how sensitive film for cameras, etc. is to light
the time taken by a camera shutter to open and close
shutter speeds

a four-speed gearbox
a ten-speed mountain bike

data.text: In senses 1 and 2 sped is also used for the past tense and past participle.
作第1及第2义时，过去式和过去分词也用sped。

data.enText: move/happen quickly
to move along quickly
He sped away on his bike.
to take sb/sth somewhere very quickly, especially in a vehicle

data.chText: 出租汽车载着他们迅速驶往市中心。
data.enText: The cab speeded them into the centre of the city.
to make sth happen more quickly

data.chText: 这些药会促进她的康复。
data.enText: The drugs will speed her recovery.
drive too fast

before.enText: usually used in the progressive tenses

data.enText: to drive faster than the speed that is legally allowed
The police caught him speeding.
speed up
speed sth↔up
to move or happen faster; to make sth move or happen faster
The train soon speeded up.

data.chText: 你能不能设法加快一点事情的进度？
data.enText: Can you try and speed things up a bit?

means: 苯丙胺，安非他明（一种兴奋剂）

ex.chText: 火车疾驶而过。
ex.enText: The train went by at high speed.

ex.chText: 这架新飞机的时速可以达到900公里。
ex.enText: This new plane can reach a speed of 900 kilometres an hour.

ex.chText: 我们必须加快送货速度。
ex.enText: We had to increase the speed of delivery.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指交通工具等运动的速率或事情发生的速度。

ex.chText: 他加快了步伐。
ex.enText: He quickened his pace.

ex.chText: 变革的步伐在加速。
ex.enText: The pace of change has accelerated.

ex.chText: 在当今世界，人类进步一日千里。
ex.enText: In the world today, mankind is progressing at a tremendous pace.

synonyms.bx: 指人步行的速度，常引申为生活、变化等的速度。

ex.chText: 他的钱用得很快，速度惊人。
ex.enText: His money was running out at an alarming rate/speed.

ex.chText: 经济增长速度放缓了。
ex.enText: The rate/speed of economic growth has slowed down.

synonyms.bx: 常指某事在一段时间内发生的速度，可与 speed 换用。

ex.chText: 喷气机正在以音速飞行。
ex.enText: The jet plane is flying at the velocity of sound.

ex.chText: 要求学生计算出光的速度。
ex.enText: The students were asked to calculate the velocity of light.

ex.chText: 豹子跑起来速度惊人。
ex.enText: Leopards can move with an astonishing velocity.

synonyms.bx: 物理学术语，指物体沿着一定方向运动时的速度；作普通意义上的速度解时，则指高速。

ex.chText: 他看了一眼手表，加快了脚步。
ex.enText: He glanced at his watch and quicken his steps.

ex.chText: 他看到苏珊时感觉自己心跳加快了。
ex.enText: He felt his heart quicken when he saw Susan.

synonyms.bx: 指增加速度、速率，尤指频率。

ex.chText: 城市化进程持续加快。
ex.enText: The urbanization process continued to accelerate.

ex.chText: 坏天气促使我们提前离开。
ex.enText: The bad weather accelerated our departure.

ex.chText: 她的车平稳地加速离开。
ex.enText: Her car accelerated smoothly away.

ex.chText: 那名赛跑运动员在转弯处突然加速。
ex.enText: That runner accelerated suddenly around the bend.

synonyms.bx: 指某事比预期更快或更早发生时，可作及物或不及物动词；指汽车或人加速时，只作不及物动词。

ex.chText: 由于一个突发事件，他提前走了。
ex.enText: His departure was hastened by an emergency.

ex.chText: 他的来信加快了调查的进程。
ex.enText: His letter hastened the course of the enquiry.

ex.chText: 糟糕的治疗加速了他的死亡。
ex.enText: Poor medical treatment hastened his death.

synonyms.bx: 多指意外、糟糕之事使某事加速，或让某事提前发生。

ex.chText: 很抱歉催你，只是董事会周四之前需要这些材料。
ex.enText: Sorry to rush you, but the board needs these materials by Thursday.

ex.chText: 他觉得自己是被催着去作决定。
ex.enText: He felt he was being rushed into making a decision.

ex.chText: 这一事件应该会促使他尽快作出决定。
ex.enText: This incident should speed his decision.

ex.chText: 这种新药应该会加快她的康复。
ex.enText: This new medicine should speed her recovery.

ex.chText: 这些新措施将加快注册过程。
ex.enText: The new measures will speed up the registration process.

synonyms.bx: 指加快某事的发生、进展等，常指好事。

tr: a central nervous system stimulant that increases energy and decreases appetite
used to treat narcolepsy and some forms of depression
a rate (usually rapid) at which something happens
example: the project advanced with gratifying speed

tr: the ratio of the focal length to the diameter of a (camera) lens system

example: The runner zipped past us at breakneck speed

tr: travel at an excessive or illegal velocity
example: I got a ticket for speeding
He rushed down the hall to receive his guests
The cars raced down the street

value.boxr_value: The form of the past tense and past participle is sped in meaning 5 but speeded for the phrasal verb. 义项 5 的过去式和过去分词为sped，但在短语动词中则为 speeded。

value.def: The speed of something is the rate at which it moves or travels.

example.ex: He drove off at high speed...
With this type of camera, the shutter speed is fixed...
example.tran: 对这类相机而言，快门的速度是固定的。

example.ex: An electrical pulse in a wire travels close to the speed of light...
example.tran: 电线里的电脉冲以接近光速的速度传输。

value.def: The speed of something is the rate at which it happens or is done.

example.ex: In the late 1850s the speed of technological change quickened...
example.tran: 19 世纪 50 年代末期，技术变革的速度加快了。

example.ex: Each learner can proceed at his own speed.
example.tran: 每一位学习者都可以按自己的进度学习。

value.tran: (某事发生或进展的)速度，进度

value.def: Speed is very fast movement or travel.

example.ex: Speed is the essential ingredient of all athletics...
example.tran: 速度是所有田径运动项目的关键要素。

example.ex: He put on a burst of speed...
The car is quite noisy at speed.
example.tran: 这辆车高速行驶时噪音很大。

value.def: Speed is a very fast rate at which something happens or is done.

example.ex: I was amazed at his speed of working.
example.tran: 他办事之麻利让我深感叹服。

example.ex: ...the sheer speed of the unification process.

value.tran: (指某事发生或进展时的)高速，快速

value.def: If you speed somewhere, you move or travel there quickly, usually in a vehicle.

example.ex: Trains will speed through the Channel Tunnel at 186mph...
example.tran: 火车将以每小时 186 英里的速度快速穿过海峡隧道。

example.ex: The engine noise rises only slightly as I speed along.
example.tran: 我一路高速行驶时，发动机的噪音只提高了一点点。

value.def: Someone who is speeding is driving a vehicle faster than the legal speed limit.

example.ex: This man was not qualified to drive and was speeding.
example.tran: 这名男子没有驾驶资格，并且违章超速行驶。

example.ex: He was fined for speeding last year.
example.tran: 他去年因超速行驶被罚了款。

value.def: Speed is an illegal drug such as amphetamine which some people take to increase their energy and excitement.
If you are up to speed, you have all the most recent information that you need about something.

example.ex: A day has been set aside to bring all councillors up to speed on the proposal...
example.tran: 已经确定了一个日子，届时将向所有的市政委员汇报有关该建议的最新进展情况。

example.ex: Those in charge deluded themselves they were up to speed.
example.tran: 那些负责人自以为掌握了最新情况。
